’›W<?php exit; ?>a:6:{s:10:"last_error";s:0:"";s:10:"last_query";s:75:"SELECT iw_posts.* FROM iw_posts WHERE ID IN (2759,2643,2504,2411,2353,2318)";s:11:"last_result";a:6:{i:0;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"2318";s:11:"post_author";s:2:"48";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-03-19 09:43:05";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-03-19 09:43:05";s:12:"post_content";s:381:"Elephants have remarkable powers of cognition; they are able to learn, remember, and experience fear, pain and loss. Â I have been so fortunate to see them interacting in the wild; I want my children and my grandchildren to have the same opportunity. Â It is up to us to be their voice; to do whatever we can to stop the illegal ivory trade, and to save this extraordinary species.";s:10:"post_title";s:12:"Jodi Picoult";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:12:"jodi-picoult";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-03-19 09:50:42";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-03-19 09:50:42";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:47:"http://iworry.org/?post_type=quotes&#038;p=2318";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:6:"quotes";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:1;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"2353";s:11:"post_author";s:2:"48";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-04-08 08:58:09";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-04-08 08:58:09";s:12:"post_content";s:322:"Elephants are facing the very real threat of extinction in the wild to feed an obsession with ivory. If we want our children to live in a world where elephants still roam free then we have to act now. Elephants deserve a place in Africa's future and it is everyoneâ€™s responsibility to ensure their survival is supported.";s:10:"post_title";s:12:"Levison Wood";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:12:"levison-wood";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-04-08 08:58:09";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-04-08 08:58:09";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:47:"http://iworry.org/?post_type=quotes&#038;p=2353";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:6:"quotes";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:2;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"2411";s:11:"post_author";s:2:"48";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-04-20 11:22:03";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-04-20 11:22:03";s:12:"post_content";s:900:"There is no difference between an elephant and myself, other than the way we look. So every time I hear of an elephant beingÂ slaughtered for their tusks, I think of my son. And how it would feel for him if I was brutally and sadistically murdered in front of him.Â And how would I feel knowing my last breaths were taken watching fear and despair on his face? Would I yell at him to run? Would I
beg for my life? Would I tell my murderers to take me somewhere else so he doesnâ€™t have to watch me be senselessly killed? I wouldÂ do all of that and more. I would fight, plead, beg, run, protect my sonâ€¦and I would hope against hope that someone somewhere outÂ there was fighting to make sure this didnâ€™t happen to others like me. How can we think the elephants arenâ€™t thinking and feeling all ofÂ these things and more? And knowing this, how can we allow this slaughter to continue to happen?";s:10:"post_title";s:11:"Alisen Down";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:11:"alisen-down";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-04-20 11:22:03";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-04-20 11:22:03";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:47:"http://iworry.org/?post_type=quotes&#038;p=2411";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:6:"quotes";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:3;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"2504";s:11:"post_author";s:2:"48";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-05-15 09:44:58";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-05-15 09:44:58";s:12:"post_content";s:664:"Our hearts bleed in the knowledge that if we continue living as we are, elephants will no longer exist in the wild ten short years from today. These magnificent creatures experience the same emotional complexity as humans and their young suffer overwhelming and prolonged grief after witnessing a parent killed for ivory. The Ian Somerhalder Foundation attests that all life on this planet isÂ interwoven and interconnected, therefore their suffering andÂ grief is ultimately OUR suffering and grief. The IS FoundationÂ stands alongside The David Sheldrick Wildlife Trust in support of their iworry campaign to stop the senseless killing of these majestic animals.";s:10:"post_title";s:15:"Ian Somerhalder";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:15:"ian-somerhalder";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-05-15 09:45:11";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-05-15 09:45:11";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:47:"http://iworry.org/?post_type=quotes&#038;p=2504";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:6:"quotes";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:4;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"2643";s:11:"post_author";s:2:"48";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-07-06 11:38:31";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-07-06 11:38:31";s:12:"post_content";s:419:"Elephant poaching is one of the most greedy, barbaric practices Iâ€™ve ever seen, and also the most traumatizing for these soulful creatures who mourn the passing of each and every family member they see slaughtered. If we donâ€™t find a resolution to this crisis, within 10 years it will be too late. The time to act is now and we all must band together to create a successful outcome and save these majestic beauties.";s:10:"post_title";s:17:"Shannon Elizabeth";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:17:"shannon-elizabeth";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-07-06 11:38:49";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-07-06 11:38:49";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:47:"http://iworry.org/?post_type=quotes&#038;p=2643";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:6:"quotes";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:5;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"2759";s:11:"post_author";s:2:"48";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-08-13 11:20:16";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-08-13 11:20:16";s:12:"post_content";s:578:"E